# Next.js 15

- The project uses Next.js 15.4.6 with React 19.1.0 and TypeScript
- Use the App Router (files in `src/app/` directory) - do not use Pages Router
- Use Turbopack for development (`next dev --turbopack`)
- Always use TypeScript for all Next.js code
- Use Server Components by default (no 'use client' directive unless needed)
- Use 'use client' directive only when using React hooks, browser APIs, or event handlers
- Use the `@/` path alias for imports (configured in tsconfig.json)
- Pages should be placed in `src/app/` directory following Next.js App Router conventions
- Use `page.tsx` for page components, `layout.tsx` for layouts, `loading.tsx` for loading states
- Use `not-found.tsx` for 404 pages
- Use `error.tsx` for error boundaries
- Use `route.ts` or `route.js` for API routes
- Use `middleware.ts` for middleware (authentication, redirects, etc.)
- Use `metadata` export or `generateMetadata` function for SEO and page metadata
- Use `generateStaticParams` for dynamic routes with static generation
- Use `useRouter()` from `next/navigation` for client-side navigation (not `next/router`)
- Use `usePathname()` and `useSearchParams()` hooks for reading URL information
- Use `Link` component from `next/link` for client-side navigation
- Use `Image` component from `next/image` for optimized images
- Use `redirect()` and `notFound()` from `next/navigation` for server-side redirects and 404s
- State management should use Zustand stores (located in `src/stores/` directory)
- Use custom hooks in `src/hooks/` directory for reusable logic
- Use Radix UI components (from `@radix-ui/*`) for accessible UI primitives
- Use shadcn/ui components (located in `src/components/ui/`) for UI components
- Use Tailwind CSS 4 for styling (configured with PostCSS)
- Use `class-variance-authority` and `clsx` with `tailwind-merge` for conditional styling
- Use Lucide React icons from `lucide-react` package
- Use `sweetalert2` for alert dialogs and confirmations
- Use `react-json-pretty` for JSON viewing in development
- Use `react-google-recaptcha` for reCAPTCHA integration
- Always use English for code, comments, and documentation
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for components
- Use kebab-case for file names in pages and routes
- Use TypeScript interfaces and types (avoid `any` type)
- Use async/await for asynchronous operations
- Use `fetch` API for data fetching (Next.js extends it with caching)
- Use environment variables with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix for client-side access
- Use server-only environment variables without prefix for server-side only
- The app supports Electron for desktop deployment (see `main.mjs` and `next.config.electron.ts`)
- Use `next lint` for linting (ESLint configured with `eslint-config-next`)
- Use Prettier for code formatting (configured in `.prettierrc`)
- Run TypeScript type checking with `tsc --noEmit` before committing
- Follow Next.js 15 best practices: leverage Server Components, use streaming, optimize images
- Use React Server Actions for form submissions and mutations
- Use `revalidate` and `revalidatePath` for cache invalidation
- Use `unstable_cache` for custom caching strategies when needed
- Use `generateStaticParams` for dynamic routes that should be pre-rendered
- Use `dynamic` import with `ssr: false` for client-only components when needed
- Use `suspense` boundaries for loading states in Server Components
- Use `loading.tsx` files for route-level loading states
- Use `error.tsx` files for route-level error handling
